<% content_for :title, "Privacy Policy · Ike" %>
<% content_for :main_class, "max-w-2xl" %>

<article class="text-[15px]">
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-1">Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-8">Last updated: June 2, 2026</p>

  <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
    Ike is a personal time-tracking tool, and your data is the whole point — so we
    keep what we collect small and we don't monetize it. This policy explains what
    we collect, why, and the choices you have. "Ike" means the service at
    <strong>iketimer.com</strong> and its companion macOS app.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">What we collect</h2>
  <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-gray-700 mb-4">
    <li><strong>Account info:</strong> your email address and the name you provide at signup.</li>
    <li><strong>Your time logs:</strong> the blocks you record — start and end times, which quadrant, and any note you write.</li>
    <li><strong>Basic technical logs:</strong> standard server logs (like IP address and request times) needed to operate and secure the service.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">Your calendar stays on your Mac</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
    If you connect a calendar, the macOS app reads your events <strong>locally on
    your device</strong> to help you label what you're working on. Your calendar is
    not sent to or stored on our servers. Only the notes you choose to save with a
    time block are synced — so if you keep a calendar-derived description in a note,
    that text is stored as part of that block.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">What we don't do</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
    We don't sell your data, we don't show ads, and we don't use third-party
    tracking or analytics to profile you. We use your information only to run Ike.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">How we use your information</h2>
  <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-gray-700 mb-4">
    <li>To store and display your time logs and trends back to you.</li>
    <li>To sync between the macOS app and the web dashboard.</li>
    <li>To email you sign-in links, confirmation links, and important service notices.</li>
    <li>To keep the service secure and to diagnose problems.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">Service providers</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
    We rely on a small number of vendors to run Ike — currently our hosting/database
    provider and our email-delivery provider. They process data only on our behalf,
    to provide their service to us. We don't share your data with anyone else except
    when required by law.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">Cookies</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
    We use a single session cookie to keep you signed in on the web. We don't use
    advertising or tracking cookies.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">Security and retention</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
    Data is encrypted in transit (HTTPS), and sign-in is passwordless using signed,
    expiring links. We keep your data for as long as your account is active. When
    you delete your account, its data is removed from active systems within 30 days
    and from backups within 60 days.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">Your rights</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
    You can ask us to access, correct, export, or delete your data at any time by
    emailing us, and we'll honor applicable privacy-law requests (such as under GDPR
    and the CCPA).
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">Children</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
    Ike isn't directed to children under 16, and we don't knowingly collect their
    data.
  </p>

  <%= render "footer" %>
</article>
